result.execSummary:
The defendant Noah M. Sanders was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Prisoner Throw/Expel Bodily Substances [Modifiers: Repeater], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.43(2m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:13am.  Clerk - CRHI. 
Defendant Noah M. Sanders in court with attorney Jeremy Christopher Evans.  Defendant Noah M. Sanders in custody.  Monica J. Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea questionnaire and rights form submitted.  Constitutional rights given.  Maximum penalties and elements recited.
The Court notes that the plea questionnaire does not include the repeater enhancement or the consent element. Court reviews the local practice of attaching the jury instructions to avoid confusion. 
During the plea colloquay, the Court establishes that there may not have been a meeting of the minds as it relates to the repeater enhancement related to Count #1. 
The Court allows counsel an opportunity to speak with his client regarding these issues and also an opportunity to contact the assigned ADA in this matter. 
Court verifies that the counsel has reviewed the consent element; that there is an agreement and that the defendant wishes to proceed today. 

Count #1 - NO CONTEST plea entered by the Def. as charged; including the repeater.  Factual basis stipulated.  Victim compliance verified.  Court accepts the plea and Finds the Def. guilty and Orders that Judgment of Conviction be entered.
State moves to read-in and dismiss Count #2; so ordered by the Court. 
Recommendations presented by Counsel.
Statement presented by the defendant. 
The Court orders: Count #1
-  5 months jail - to be served in the prison system consecutive to any other sentences in being. The defendant has no credit for time served. 
-  $268 costs and $250 DNA surcharge.  Payment of the financial obligations is ordered at the rate of $35 per month starting 2/28/2019. Failure to pay as ordered will result in 11 days jail consecutive. 
-  DNA surcharge compliance upon request.
